    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Available is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the high-revving 3.6L M96 flat-six engine mated to a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This example showcases the mechanical purity of the naturally aspirated boxer engine, utilizing VarioCam Plus for optimized torque across the rev range. The chassis dynamics are sharp, benefiting from a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry that retains excellent damping characteristics. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row retrofit, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) is dry, indicating a well-maintained drivetrain. Braking performance remains consistent via four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response are precise, making this an ideal driver\u2019s car for the purist seeking a communicative rear-engine experience.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 42
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Used sedan. Reliable daily driver. Clean interior. Regular oil changes. Minor exterior scuffs. Good condition. $34,500.",
